1
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:13,199
You two,

2
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,839
Are you here to eat or to stay?

3
00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:15,800
One superior room.

4
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,919
One room facing the street.

5
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,880
The cheapest room.

6
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:18,600
Sir,

7
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,240
Rooms facing the street are noisy.

8
00:02:20,479 --> 00:02:22,160
I'm particular about beds.

9
00:02:22,279 --> 00:02:23,679
I won't be able to sleep.

10
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:24,720
You take the superior room.

11
00:02:25,559 --> 00:02:26,759
Me, in the superior room?

12
00:02:27,479 --> 00:02:28,600
Do I need to repeat myself?

13
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:29,759
No need, no need.

14
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,119
But...

15
00:02:31,639 --> 00:02:34,119
If I take the superior room and you take the street-facing one,

16
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,720
that's not appropriate.

17
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,960
You're delicate and precious.

18
00:02:37,039 --> 00:02:38,360
I don't want it to be the other way around,

19
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:40,000
having to take care of someone with a sore back and legs.

20
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,320
How do you know

21
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,360
I'd get a sore back and legs from a cheap bed?

22
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,639
I... I've never told you before.

23
00:02:49,839 --> 00:02:50,639
I didn't expect

24
00:02:50,679 --> 00:02:51,960
you cared so much about me.

25
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:52,919
It's fine.

26
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:54,119
If you don't want to, I'll take it back.

27
00:02:54,479 --> 00:02:56,279
Don't! Please, you two, stop arguing.

28
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:59,639
Our inn only has one side room facing the street left.

29
00:03:01,639 --> 00:03:02,720
It's fine, it's fine.

30
00:03:02,839 --> 00:03:04,360
We can make do.

31
00:03:06,119 --> 00:03:06,800
Sir,

32
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:09,000
We're here on official business, so priorities come first.

33
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:09,639
A room facing the street

34
00:03:09,679 --> 00:03:11,240
makes it easier to observe the surroundings.

35
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,520
Please just make do.

36
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,600
Old man,

37
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,160
young wife,

38
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,440
you're quite lucky in love.

39
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,240
We're not— Thank you, boss.

40
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,039
Go tell them.

41
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,279
Where we're staying.

42
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,919
Why is it me again?

43
00:03:36,119 --> 00:03:37,399
This is a temporary assistant.

44
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,559
Things that need to be done.

45
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:40,880
And also,

46
00:03:41,039 --> 00:03:42,600
Bring all our luggage over.

47
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:44,919
Me?

48
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,119
Hurry, go!

49
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,360
Faster!

50
00:03:56,039 --> 00:03:56,839
Don't come over here!

51
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:00,440
Give my mother back to me!

52
00:04:00,479 --> 00:04:01,679
Give her back!

53
00:04:01,919 --> 00:04:02,720
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

54
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,160
He's a madman.

55
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,240
Village chief.

56
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,039
Why keep such a menace around?

57
00:04:07,199 --> 00:04:08,839
Just kill him to avenge the village women.

58
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,080
Kill him! Kill him! Kill him!

59
00:04:14,559 --> 00:04:15,960
It's true that a murderer should pay with his life.

60
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,200
But everything should be handled by the authorities according to the law.

61
00:04:18,279 --> 00:04:18,799
In a few days,

62
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:20,600
it will be the day when the miasma forest disappears for a month.

63
00:04:20,679 --> 00:04:21,279
I suggest

64
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,399
we detain him for now.

65
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,559
What if he escapes in the meantime?

66
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:25,079
He should be torn to pieces.

67
00:04:27,359 --> 00:04:28,399
Everyone, calm down.

68
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,640
If we take justice into our own hands,

69
00:04:29,679 --> 00:04:31,279
how are we any different from the murderer?

70
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:32,959
You're an outsider woman meddling in our village's affairs.

71
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,920
We want revenge!

72
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,440
Revenge—yes, we want revenge!

73
00:04:35,559 --> 00:04:36,640
Everyone, calm down!

74
00:04:40,239 --> 00:04:41,320
Linlang, are you okay?

75
00:04:41,359 --> 00:04:42,040
I'm fine.

76
00:04:42,559 --> 00:04:43,200
Doctor Li,

77
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:44,079
You are highly respected.

78
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,320
Why don't you say something?

79
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,880
I can't see.

80
00:04:47,959 --> 00:04:49,519
They can't hear.

81
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:50,760
Whether I speak or not,

82
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,239
what difference does it make?

83
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:54,799
Doctor Li,

84
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:56,959
Linlang,

85
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,399
Don't be impulsive.

86
00:04:58,559 --> 00:05:00,160
They're monsters and beasts now.

87
00:05:00,239 --> 00:05:01,279
If you go, you won't be able to save him,

88
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,440
and you'll only hurt yourself.

89
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:03,079
That's right.

90
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,279
He's not wrong.

91
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:06,079
But I can't just stand by and watch

92
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:07,239
Ergou get killed.

93
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:08,760
Linlang,

94
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,359
Beat him to death!

95
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,239
Hit him!

96
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,000
Hit!

97
00:05:15,799 --> 00:05:16,880
Hit! Hit!

98
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:18,720
Avenge him!

99
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,959
Beat him to death!

100
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,040
Why is it raining?

101
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:23,320
It's raining.

102
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,519
Beat him to death!

103
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,239
Drink the ginger soup.

104
00:05:50,799 --> 00:05:51,760
Warm yourself up.

105
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,760
This case is about to be closed.

106
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,399
The miasma in the Miasma Forest

107
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,720
dissipates once a month.

108
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:06,799
We need to get ready to set out.

109
00:06:08,279 --> 00:06:09,760
But Sima Kong's injury—

110
00:06:09,839 --> 00:06:11,000
Sima Kong's injury

111
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,079
is just a cover.

112
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,959
You want to stay.

113
00:06:14,799 --> 00:06:15,839
How did you know?

114
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,720
You usually don't hide it.

115
00:06:17,839 --> 00:06:18,640
When something's on your mind,

116
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,839
it's easy to tell.

117
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,000
You want to stay

118
00:06:21,079 --> 00:06:22,079
and keep investigating the case.

119
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:22,799
Lu Jiu,

120
00:06:23,239 --> 00:06:25,320
I know that going to Mist Town to find out your brother's whereabouts

121
00:06:25,399 --> 00:06:27,119
is the most important thing for us right now.

122
00:06:27,359 --> 00:06:28,959
If we miss this chance,

123
00:06:29,119 --> 00:06:31,399
we'll have to wait over a month before we can leave here again.

124
00:06:35,119 --> 00:06:36,119
Actually,

125
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:38,799
my trip to Mist Town

126
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,519
isn't just for my brother.

127
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,399
Why did you bring me here?

128
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,519
When the body was first discovered,

129
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,119
I came here with the villagers.

130
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:04,119
The body was here.

131
00:07:04,559 --> 00:07:05,839
On that wall over there,

132
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:07,480
are the scratch marks left by Ergou.

133
00:07:07,519 --> 00:07:08,320
It was me.

134
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,519
Those scratch marks

135
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,760
were left by me.

136
00:07:15,559 --> 00:07:17,200
Young Master, everything is fine.

137
00:07:18,279 --> 00:07:19,440
You went through so much trouble

138
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:20,920
to get here through the miasma forest

139
00:07:21,119 --> 00:07:22,239
just to greet me?

140
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:23,040
No.

141
00:07:23,079 --> 00:07:24,239
I discovered

142
00:07:24,359 --> 00:07:25,399
that Inspector Geng Zhao

143
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,279
is lying in wait outside the miasma forest.

144
00:07:27,799 --> 00:07:28,679
His goal

145
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,119
is probably the same as Lian Buci's.

146
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,679
He just wants to capture Lu Jiu and take him back.

147
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:32,760
He is nothing to fear.

148
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,679
The information you asked me to investigate

149
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,839
I have already found out.

150
00:07:36,239 --> 00:07:37,040
Tiger Claw Fist

151
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:39,160
is a unique martial art of Tianluo.

152
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,399
In the past ten years,

153
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,079
the Tianluo leader, Dugu,

154
00:07:42,239 --> 00:07:43,440
has only taught it to one person.

155
00:07:43,559 --> 00:07:44,799
That is his adopted son,

156
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:45,720
Fei Ying.

157
00:07:46,359 --> 00:07:47,160
Fei Ying.

158
00:07:47,559 --> 00:07:50,160
The top assassin of Wuxiang City who disappeared years ago.

159
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:51,359
Before he disappeared,

160
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,519
Dugu sent him

161
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,760
to work as a secret tomb raider.

162
00:07:55,119 --> 00:07:55,959
That year,

163
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,640
he was only thirteen.

164
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,559
Thirteen years ago,

165
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,119
I fell seriously ill.

166
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,720
When I woke up, I couldn't remember anything.

167
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:08,640
Are you blind or something?

168
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,359
These tiger claws

169
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,760
are indeed the same as your previous fighting style.

170
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,839
But judging from the marks,

171
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,519
it should be a weapon like a blade.

172
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,679
I've never seen a blade shaped like tiger claws.

173
00:08:25,119 --> 00:08:26,559
Ever since I entered this village,

174
00:08:26,679 --> 00:08:28,359
I've had a strange sense of familiarity.

175
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:29,920
I remember you said before

176
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,920
that you had a serious illness as a child,

177
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:34,520
and lost all your memories afterward.

178
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:35,840
Could it be...

179
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:37,559
I'm not sure.

180
00:08:38,119 --> 00:08:38,919
But

181
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,919
everything

182
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:43,159
should be related to Mist Village.

183
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,840
How did you find out?

184
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,200
Come with me.

185
00:08:53,239 --> 00:08:54,000
Earlier

186
00:08:54,359 --> 00:08:56,239
I was in my elder brother's study's secret room

187
00:08:56,359 --> 00:08:58,719
and found a map pointing to Mist Town

188
00:08:59,159 --> 00:09:00,640
So Sima Kong and I

189
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,359
decided to travel together

190
00:09:03,719 --> 00:09:05,239
And recently, in my memory

191
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:06,840
this map

192
00:09:08,239 --> 00:09:09,559
appeared right here

193
00:09:12,719 --> 00:09:14,200
Fei Ying was still young at the time

194
00:09:14,239 --> 00:09:16,039
small in stature but exceptionally skilled in martial arts

195
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,599
a promising candidate for tomb raiding

196
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,320
But Tian Luo's goal

197
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:20,719
is probably not just tomb raiding

198
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:22,159
or simply earning a few coins

199
00:09:22,239 --> 00:09:23,960
So, Young Master means

200
00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:26,919
the burial items in this ancient tomb

201
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,559
are related to the Wuxiang treasure

202
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,520
Send a message by carrier pigeon immediately

203
00:09:30,599 --> 00:09:31,440
and report to the sect leader

204
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,400
Yes

205
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,719
It's just that

206
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:35,719
Just what?

207
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,440
If the sect leader asks

208
00:09:37,479 --> 00:09:39,039
how you knew

209
00:09:39,239 --> 00:09:40,599
about Tiger Claw Fist

210
00:09:44,719 --> 00:09:46,000
Among the assassins who tried to kill Lu Jiu,

211
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:47,719
someone once used Tiger Claw Fist.

212
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:48,320
Hmm.

213
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,520
That makes sense.

214
00:09:51,719 --> 00:09:52,599
But...

215
00:09:53,479 --> 00:09:54,559
What's wrong now?

216
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:57,039
Young Master,

217
00:09:57,239 --> 00:09:59,039
have you recently

218
00:09:59,119 --> 00:10:00,760
experienced a sudden rapid heartbeat

219
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,719
or a flushed face?

220
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,159
I think I have.

221
00:10:04,239 --> 00:10:05,119
Why do you ask?

222
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,520
This place is beautiful and secluded,

223
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:10,200
between men and women,

224
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:12,119
it's easy for feelings to develop.

225
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,280
My heart belongs only to Tang Sect.

226
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,719
I've never been tempted by romance.

227
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:17,479
No, no, no.

228
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,440
What I mean is,

229
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,320
Lu Jiu

230
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:24,159
Lu Jiu and Lin Lang are close.

231
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,320
If they develop feelings for each other

232
00:10:26,479 --> 00:10:27,479
and join forces,

233
00:10:27,599 --> 00:10:30,119
wouldn't it be harder for you to gather information?

234
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:30,919
I understand.

235
00:10:31,039 --> 00:10:31,960
You may go.

236
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:33,719
Alright.

237
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,640
Why are you back so late?

238
00:10:48,799 --> 00:10:49,599
How did it go?

239
00:10:50,119 --> 00:10:51,080
Everything is normal.

240
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:52,719
Why are you still awake?

241
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,880
These past few days, I noticed the top shelf of the medicine cabinet

242
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,039
has many rarely used medicines

243
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,039
that have already gone bad.

244
00:10:57,119 --> 00:10:59,119
So I reorganized them and moved them to the lower shelf

245
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,280
to make it easier for Doctor Li to access.

246
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:02,719
Miss Xu,

247
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,919
thank you so much.

248
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:07,919
A few years ago, I could still see.

249
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,320
So I made the medicine cabinet a bit taller.

250
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,200
Later, I lost my sight.

251
00:11:12,359 --> 00:11:14,919
It became inconvenient to move the cabinet, so I left it as it was.

252
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,640
So you could see before?

253
00:11:17,359 --> 00:11:18,400
Yes.

254
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:20,119
My wife and I

255
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,919
were childhood sweethearts.

256
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,719
We studied medicine and made medicines together.

257
00:11:24,239 --> 00:11:26,719
Sadly, she passed away suddenly.

258
00:11:27,760 --> 00:11:29,320
I cried every day.

259
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,719
And my eyes...

260
00:11:34,359 --> 00:11:35,400
Speaking of which,

261
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,080
this cabinet

262
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,599
was made when my wife and I got married.

263
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,440
Back then,

264
00:11:41,719 --> 00:11:44,679
my wife would help me organize these herbs every day, just like Miss Xu does now.

265
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:46,679
She helped me sort these medicinal herbs.

266
00:11:48,119 --> 00:11:48,919
In the blink of an eye,

267
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,200
so many years have passed.

268
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:53,559
Doctor Li,

269
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:55,119
please accept our condolences.

270
00:11:58,039 --> 00:11:58,960
We

271
00:11:59,159 --> 00:12:00,599
have disturbed you for quite a long time.

272
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,919
It's about time for us to leave.

273
00:12:05,119 --> 00:12:06,440
You're leaving?

274
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:08,479
I've already checked.

275
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:10,599
The miasma will clear by tomorrow morning.

276
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:11,960
We can set out then.

277
00:12:12,559 --> 00:12:14,200
Since my wife passed away,

278
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,719
this humble cottage of mine

279
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,520
hasn't been this lively for many years.

280
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:20,880
Once you leave,

281
00:12:21,719 --> 00:12:23,359
I'll truly miss you.

282
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,359
Doctor Li,

283
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:25,640
once we've finished our business,

284
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:26,960
we'll come back to visit you.

285
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,320
That's good.

286
00:12:29,479 --> 00:12:30,479
